{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nThe 2026-07-12 calibration analysis (session logs remarkable-hydrated-nightjar / tainted-continuing-queensnake / shaggy-linoleum-gavial) found: (1) code review is too loose — 0 'BLOCK — finding' votes across 162 post-recalibration changes while confirmed must-fix findings sailed through as advisories (change #529's untested-degradation advisory scored impact 0.0 and went red on main 57 minutes after merge; #518's importlib code-execution findings at 0.54; #539's correctness findings at 0.60 — against a 0.95 threshold no real finding ever reached); (2) plan-review advisory load is protocol-inflated — CLAUDE.md mandates remediating ALL valid advisories (~13/round, 95% of remediation edits mint new findings), and with the convergence floors now default-ON (change 562) we want to observe organic agent behavior instead of mandated remediation; (3) completion-verifier defects are structural, not admissibility: FAIL verdicts persist nowhere, FAILs ratchet piecemeal (3b4e took 2 extra CI cycles), and 'children closed (signed)' epic ACs defeat the certifiable:false escape hatch (bf50/5f39 contagion, bug 02a3).\n\n## Definitions & Sequencing\n- **\"serious-tier\" (Success Criterion 1):** the code-review criteria whose findings map to the SERIOUS (0.9) consequence binaries in `src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/decide.py` — prod-lane `data_loss_without_recovery`, `security_bypass_not_enforced_elsewhere`, `silent_wrong_feeding_a_decision`; maint-lane `unversioned_published_contract_break`, `safety_net_removal_without_replacement` — plus the `security` criterion. Child b9c0 enumerates the exact enabled set and pins it in a test; everything else stays advisory at 0.95.\n- **code-v2 vs code-v3 cohort ordering (f32e vs 9f25/b9c0):** 9f25 derives, and b9c0 enables, a block threshold over the existing **code-v2** finding cohort — valid for code-v2 sidecars only. f32e adds a new maint binary and bumps `IMPACT_MODEL_VERSION` to **code-v3**, which per ADR-0036 starts a FRESH calibration cohort. Re-deriving/enabling any threshold over code-v3 is explicitly a FUTURE follow-up, NOT part of b9c0 — no threshold in this epic consumes code-v3. The two workstreams are independent by design; there is no ordering dependency between f32e and 9f25/b9c0, and b9c0's threshold governs code-v2 findings regardless of f32e's landing order.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Code-review blocking is derived from adjudicated field data (the crossover threshold where a finding is more likely correctly-blocking than false-blocking), enabled for the serious-tier criteria (defined above), and passes the ADR-0036 A/B gate before flipping.\n- Agent guidance no longer MANDATES advisory remediation (loosened to judgment, NOT reversed), so post-change review rounds measure organic advisory uptake.\n- Completion-verifier FAILs are durably persisted and enumerate all unmet criteria in one verdict; the signed-children AC anti-pattern is documented.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] All child tickets (the epic's work items) are closed, each with its change landed on main.\n- [ ] An in-session measurement-framework artifact is recorded as a comment on this epic: (a) the pre-change BASELINE from the 2026-07-12 analysis (0 finding-blocks / 162 changes; ~13 advisories/round), (b) the exact re-runnable queries/commands for post-change measurement — code-review block/false-block counts from the `REVIEW_RESULT` (code_review_result_v1) sidecars, and plan-review advisory-uptake via `norm_id` survival across rounds — and (c) a link to the deferred follow-up ticket that will record the ACTUAL post-deployment field data. (This is created at merge time and IS verifiable in-session; the actual multi-day telemetry is explicitly deferred, below.)\n- [ ] The deferred post-deployment measurement is filed as a separate follow-up ticket (72b6-b0d2-2f93-456d, linked `discovered_from` this epic, parked in `idea`), whose data-collection criterion is `[operator-attested]`. That telemetry is OUT of this epic's close path: this epic closes on the measurement FRAMEWORK being in place, not on multi-day field data existing."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783883781323721001,"uuid":"dc697b2c-5baf-4358-b1cf-ad648458542f"}